<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-11T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-11T20:00:00-05:00" n="900" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits/648:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-11T20:00:00-05:00">October 11, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>333. Executive Order 8565, October 10, 1940<note n="12" xml:id="d900fn12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Federal Register</hi>, October 12, 1940, p.
                                    4062.</note> extended all provisions of Executive Order 8389 of
                                April 10, 1940,<note n="13" xml:id="d900fn13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, April 12, 1940, pp. 1400–1401.
                                    This order froze all the assets of Denmark and Norway in the
                                    United States.</note> as amended, to include Rumania. For
                                reference see last paragraph of Radio Bulletin No. 85, April 10,
                                1940.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>